---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title = "BC PNP Processing Times 2025: Current Wait Periods";
const description = "Current BC PNP processing times for Skills Immigration, Express Entry, and Entrepreneur streams. Learn what affects your application speed.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 py-12 px-4 sm:px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8">
      
      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="space-y-4 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-tight">
          BC PNP <span class="text-green-600">Processing Times</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          How long does it take to get nominated? Here are the latest estimated processing times for 2025 across all streams.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none bg-white p-8 sm:p-12 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm">
        
        <h2>Skills Immigration Processing Times</h2>
        <p>
            This category includes Skilled Worker, International Graduate, and Entry Level & Semi-Skilled streams.
        </p>
        
        <div class="not-prose overflow-x-auto my-6">
            <table class="min-w-full text-left text-sm">
                <thead class="bg-gray-100 border-b border-gray-200">
                    <tr>
                        <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-slate-900">Stream</th>
                        <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-slate-900">Estimated Time</th>
                        <th class="px-4 py-3 font-bold text-slate-900">Notes</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
                     <tr>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Generic Skills Immigration</td>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 font-bold">2 - 3 Months</td>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">Standard processing</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">BC PNP Tech</td>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 font-bold">2 - 3 Months</td>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">Often faster due to priority</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Health Authority</td>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 font-bold">2 - 3 Months</td>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">Priority processing</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Entry Level & Semi-Skilled</td>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 font-bold">3 - 4 Months</td>
                        <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">May require more verification</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-xl text-sm border border-slate-200 mb-8">
            <strong>Note:</strong> This time starts from the day you submit your <em>complete application</em> (after receiving an invitation), not from the day you register in SIRS.
        </div>

        <h2>Federal Processing (After Nomination)</h2>
        <p>
            Getting the provincial nomination is only half the battle. You then apply to the federal government (IRCC) for permanent residence. This stage takes longer.
        </p>

        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 not-prose">
            <div class="border border-slate-200 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <div class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Express Entry</div>
                <div class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-1">5 - 8 Months</div>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Online system. Much faster.</p>
            </div>
             <div class="border border-slate-200 p-6 rounded-2xl">
                <div class="text-xs font-bold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-2">Non-Express Entry</div>
                <div class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-1">11 - 18 Months</div>
                <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Paper-based/Portal. Slower.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-12">Factors That Delay Processing</h2>
        <p>
            Your application might move slower than average if:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Incomplete Documents:</strong> Missing signatures, blurry scans, or wrong forms.</li>
            <li><strong>Employer Verification:</strong> If BC PNP cannot reach your employer to verify your job offer.</li>
            <li><strong>Complexity:</strong> Unusual business structures or complex work history.</li>
            <li><strong>Volume:</strong> If there is a sudden spike in applications (e.g., after a large draw).</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Speed It Up?</h2>
        <p>
            You cannot pay for faster processing. The only way to ensure the fastest possible result is to:
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Triple-check your checklist:</strong> Don't miss a single file.</li>
            <li><strong>Inform your employer:</strong> Tell them BC PNP might call or email, and to respond quickly.</li>
            <li><strong>Use the Tech Stream:</strong> If eligible, it is prioritized.</li>
        </ol>

      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
